Class ScalablePushRegistry

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.confluent.ksql.physical.scalablepush.ScalablePushRegistry
  • All Implemented Interfaces:

    public class ScalablePushRegistry
extends java.lang.Object
implements org.apache.kafka.streams.processor.api.ProcessorSupplier<java.lang.Object,GenericRow,java.lang.Void,java.lang.Void>
    This registry is kept with every persistent query, peeking at the stream which is the output of the topology. These rows are then fed to any registered ProcessingQueues where they are eventually passed on to scalable push queries.
